    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Right, so if the goal is a \"super-fine\" finish that maintains a high level of protection/separation from the environment, is there a specific ratio of warp to weft that we should be looking for to ensure the most \"impenetrable\" or closed-off surface texture?",
      "source": "evaluator",
